## Advantages of DevOps

- Faster software development
- Better collaboration between teams
- Automated testing and deployment
- Improved software quality
- Faster bug fixing
- Continuous monitoring
- Reduced manual work

---

## Limitations

- Requires team collaboration
- Initial setup can be time-consuming
- Learning DevOps tools takes time
- Automation infrastructure needs maintenance

---

## Real-Time Example

Suppose a developer fixes a bug in an online shopping application.

- The developer pushes the code to GitHub.
- Jenkins or GitHub Actions automatically builds the project.
- Automated tests are executed.
- If all tests pass, Docker creates the application image.
- The application is deployed automatically to the server.
- Monitoring tools check whether the application is running correctly.

This entire process happens with minimal manual effort.

